---

## 1. Model Details

> What model or API is being used? Who built it? What version? What type of
> model — classification, prediction, generation, optimization? When was it
> developed?

[The NutriGuide system is an AI recommendation system combining collaborative filtering and constraint-based optimization to generate personalized weekly meal plans and shopping lists. It is trained on nutritional databases, grocery pricing data, and dietary guidelines.

The system also incorporates a natural language processing (NLP) component to support basic user queries.

It was developed by a university research team in partnership with a nonprofit organization focused on food security, and funded through a USDA grant. A specific model version is not provided, which shows that this is an early-stage or pilot deployment system.]

---

## 2. Intended Use

> What is the primary task? Who are the intended users? What decisions does
> the system inform? In what context is it deployed?

[This system is meant to be a healthy food recommendation system, specifically meant to help low income families in underserved urban neighborhoods in order to enable them make healthy food choices. The primary users of the tool are parents, caregivers in household earning below 200% of the federal poverty level. 
The system informs decisions related to: Weekly meal planning, Grocery purchasing within budget constraints, Healthier food substitutions. It is deployed as a mobile application and kiosk-based system in community health centers and WIC offices.]

