## 3. Out-of-Scope Uses

> What should this system NOT be used for? What populations, settings, or
> decisions are outside its design? What misuses are foreseeable?

[It would be inappropriate for anyone to use this tool, which is a healthy food recommendation system to manage any chronic conditions that they may be battling with; like heart diseases or type 2 diabetes.
That would mean that the tool is being used in the wrong context for the wrong purpose.
Also, currently, the tool does not fully handle cultural food preferences so expecting the tool to provide tailor-made recommendations based on one's cultural preferences would be out of the tool's scope.]

