## 5. Evaluation Data & Metrics

> How was performance measured? What metrics were used — accuracy, sensitivity,
> specificity, F1, AUC, RMSE? On what test set? Is it independent from the
> training data?

[No formal evaluation framework is described in the system documentation. Current feedback mechanisms rely on user ratings and substitution behavior, which are insufficient for thorough  validation.

Recommended evaluation metrics include:
Recommendation accuracy (precision/recall)
User adherence rate (did users follow meal plans/ the foods that were recommended by the system?)
Nutritional adequacy scores (was healthy eating really achieved by the users of this tool?)
Cost-efficiency metrics (nutrition per dollar - how much were they really able to save, compared to where they would have defaulted to go shopping.)
User satisfaction scores (beyond simple ratings. Aside just the rating, what was used to measure the satisfaction of a user)

Also, an independent test dataset separate from training data should be used to evaluate the performance of this tool.]

