## 8. Limitations & Caveats

> Known failure modes, edge cases, what the model does not capture. Conditions
> where it performs poorly. Assumptions baked into the design that may not
> hold in all deployment contexts.

[One major limitation of the tool is that it lacks cultural context or consideration. If the tool recommends a meal that they cannot really relate to, that recommendation will become useless to the users.
Also, it currently does not account for other food allergies but just 6. That can be a problem if some individuals have other allergies aside the 6 that the tool covers. Another thing worth mentioning is that the tool
assumes that the target population has constant access to the food stores/sources even though this may not really be the case for some households.]

