## 9. Human Oversight

> Who reviews outputs before action is taken? Human in the loop, on the loop,
> or out of the loop? What is the escalation path when the model is wrong?
> Can it act autonomously — and should it?

[Another limitation of this tool is that it lacks human oversight. There is no dietitian or nutritionist that serves as the human in the loop to ensure that the meals or foods recommended are safe for these families.
This tool should not be aloud to work autonomously, there has to be a form oversight.

Recommendation :

Incorporate dietitians or nutritionists as reviewers (human-in-the-loop)
Community health workers could act as on-the-loop supervisors during WIC visits
Provide an escalation pathway for:
Allergy concerns
Medical dietary needs
Incorrect recommendations]

